        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 19 at 10:34AM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 1032 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Genoa, moving northeast at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Huntley, Union, and Hampshire.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
